      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">PGI 225.7018-4</ph> Nonavailability
determination.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p rev="Revised October 1, 2020"
            outputclass="List1"
            class="- topic/p ">(a)
Individual nonavailability determinations.</p>
         <p rev="Revised October 1, 2020"
            outputclass="List2"
            class="- topic/p ">(2) Contracting
officers may use the following template for individual nonavailability
determinations under this section:</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">SUBJECT: Individual Nonavailability Determination Exception under
DFARS <xref href="https://www.acq.osd.mil/dpap/dars/pgi/pgi_htm/current/PGI225_70.htm"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">225.7018-4</xref>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">PROGRAM, ITEM, OR PART DESCRIPTION: _____________________________</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">CONTRACT OR SOLICITATION NUMBER: ________________________________</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">BACKGROUND: Per the requirements of 10 U.S.C. 2533c, DFARS <xref href="https://www.acq.osd.mil/dpap/dars/pgi/pgi_htm/current/PGI225_70.htm"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">252.225-7052</xref> prohibits
acquisition of samarium-cobalt magnets, neodymium-iron-boron magnets,
tantalum metal and alloys, tungsten metal powder, and tungsten heavy
alloy or any finished or semi-finished component containing tungsten
heavy alloy melted or produced in North Korea, China, Russia, and Iran.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Per DFARS <xref href="https://www.acq.osd.mil/dpap/dars/pgi/pgi_htm/current/PGI225_70.htm"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">225.7018-4</xref> , the Head
of Contracting Activity (HCA) can authorize an exception to DFARS <xref href="https://www.acq.osd.mil/dpap/dars/pgi/pgi_htm/current/PGI225_70.htm"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">252.225-7052</xref> through
an ‘Individual Nonavailability Determination’ if they determine
that covered materials of satisfactory quality and quantity, in
the required form, cannot be procured as and when needed at a reasonable
price from a source other than a covered country.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">ANALYSIS OF ALTERNATIVES:</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">See Attachment A for an analysis of why alternatives that would
not require a nonavailability determination are unacceptable.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">CERTIFICATION: Based on the satisfactory quality, quantity, required
form, timeliness, and/or reasonable price issues described in Attachment
A, I hereby certify that the requirements for an individual nonavailability
determination under DFARS <xref href="https://www.acq.osd.mil/dpap/dars/pgi/pgi_htm/current/PGI225_70.htm"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">225.7018-4</xref> have been
met.</p>
